1. Login to Azure Portal

Go to portal.azure.com and sign in.
Select Virtual Machines from the left side.

2. Create Virtual Machine

Click Create → Azure Virtual Machine.
Enter basic details like VM name and region.

3. Choose Operating System

Select one OS image:

Ubuntu Linux

Windows Server

4. Choose VM Size

Select B1s, which is the free-tier virtual machine.

5. Configure Administrator Login

Linux → upload SSH key

Windows → create username and password

6. Networking Settings

Enable inbound port:

SSH (22) for Linux

RDP (3389) for Windows

7. Review and Create

Click Review + Create, then Create.

8. Connect to VM

Linux → use SSH command from your terminal

Windows → download RDP file and log in

9. Capture VM Details

Take screenshots of:

VM Overview Page

Public IP

Successful connection
